WEBVTT

00:01.800 --> 00:03.400
Hey, Charlie, would you
see who that is?!

00:11.300 --> 00:12.600
It's Death!

00:13.700 --> 00:14.700
Hi, Mom!

00:17.900 --> 00:19.800
Your gardener left this
in the driveway.

00:20.800 --> 00:23.000
It wasn't a gardener,
it was a girl with a grudge.

00:27.400 --> 00:28.900
So how
was your friend's funeral?

00:28.900 --> 00:31.100
Oh! Terribly disappointing.

00:31.400 --> 00:32.600
Yeah, in my experience,

00:32.600 --> 00:35.100
nothing kills a party
like a dead broad in a box.

00:37.400 --> 00:39.100
Don't be glib, Charlie.

00:39.300 --> 00:40.000
Hello, Alan.

00:40.300 --> 00:41.300
Oh, hey, Mom.

00:41.300 --> 00:42.800
Wow, you look nice.

00:43.300 --> 00:45.200
Yes, mourning becomes me,
doesn't it?

00:45.600 --> 00:47.400
If only more
of my friends would die.

00:48.300 --> 00:50.000
I'm sure the feeling's mutual.

00:51.800 --> 00:53.700
Charlie, as long
as you're over there,

00:53.700 --> 00:55.000
make Mommy a drink.

00:55.100 --> 00:56.900
It's been
a very depressing afternoon.

00:57.100 --> 00:58.500
Thanks for spreading
it around.

00:59.300 --> 01:02.100
Can you believe,
two of Cynthia's three children

01:02.500 --> 01:05.099
didn't even bother showing up
at her funeral?

01:05.400 --> 01:08.500
And the one who did was drunk
and cracking tasteless jokes

01:08.600 --> 01:10.500
about his mother
all throughout the service.

01:11.300 --> 01:13.600
You didn't happen
to jot any of them
down, did you?

01:16.400 --> 01:18.100
And it wasn't just the children.

01:18.100 --> 01:20.100
The crowd was very sparse

01:20.200 --> 01:22.700
and there
was virtually no mournin

01:23.000 --> 01:24.200
Well, that's understandable,
isn't it?

01:24.300 --> 01:25.600
You said no one really liked
this woman.

01:25.700 --> 01:28.200
Oh, she was a hateful shrew,
but still.

01:29.700 --> 01:30.700
Fortunately,

01:30.700 --> 01:32.600
I was able to draw
on my theater background

01:32.600 --> 01:33.800
and work up a good cry.

01:35.000 --> 01:36.500
Sense-memory.

01:36.900 --> 01:38.000
I remember the time

01:38.400 --> 01:41.100
<i>I wasn't cast as Blanche Dubois
in Streetcar.</i>

01:42.000 --> 01:43.300
You're a good friend, Mom.

01:44.300 --> 01:47.700
I know. I'm just glad
that when my time comes,

01:47.700 --> 01:50.500
I won't have such
a humiliating sendoff.

01:54.600 --> 01:55.100
Right?

01:55.200 --> 01:56.900
Oh, yeah, yeah, sure.
Of course.

01:58.400 --> 01:59.800
Well, I'm going
to go eshen up.

01:59.900 --> 02:02.800
Even fake tears can ruin
one's mascara.

02:03.600 --> 02:04.100
Speaking of which,

02:04.100 --> 02:06.000
whoever did Cynthia's makeup
should be shot

02:06.000 --> 02:07.000
and buried beside her.

02:07.100 --> 02:09.199
She looked
like a varnished clown.

02:10.699 --> 02:12.200
You'll go to Mom's
funeral, won't you?

02:13.800 --> 02:16.000
Of course.
As the eldest son,

02:16.000 --> 02:20.400
it's my obligation
to pound in the stake.

02:20.400 --> 02:22.300
Typical--
nothing for Alan to do.

02:22.500 --> 02:24.900
Okay, you can
cut off her head

02:24.900 --> 02:26.900
and hold it up
for the villagers.

02:27.700 --> 02:30.500
www.1000fr.com present

02:30.600 --> 02:33.600
sync:FRM@Ó²°î°î

02:33.700 --> 02:34.500
What are you doing?

02:35.200 --> 02:37.400
Leaving before Mom gets out
of the bathroom.

02:38.400 --> 02:39.700
I thought we were taking her
to dinne

02:39.900 --> 02:41.500
I can't listen to her anymore.

02:42.400 --> 02:44.400
It just blows my mind
that she can go on and on

02:44.400 --> 02:46.200
about her toxic friend's
sad little funeral

02:46.200 --> 02:49.200
when we both know she's going
to end up exactly the same way!

02:49.300 --> 02:50.100
I don't disagree,

02:50.600 --> 02:52.200
but there's an option
to running away from her.

02:52.200 --> 02:53.600
Yeah, but we'd get caught

02:53.600 --> 02:55.100
and you'd sell me out
for a reduced sentence.

02:56.200 --> 02:57.900
<i>We could tell
her the truth;</i>

02:58.200 --> 03:00.000
that she's just as toxic
as her late friend

03:00.100 --> 03:02.200
and that that's the way
she's gonna be remembered.

03:05.300 --> 03:06.900
Are you on crack?

03:06.900 --> 03:09.100
Maybe if she realized
how people see her,

03:09.200 --> 03:10.800
she might make an effort
to change.

03:10.800 --> 03:12.800
If she realized how people
see her,

03:12.800 --> 03:14.800
she'd just get new people.

03:15.600 --> 03:17.000
What are we
gonna say, Alan?

03:17.100 --> 03:18.500
"Hey, Mom,
you're a crazy she-bat

03:18.600 --> 03:20.300
"and the only way people will
come to your funeral

03:20.400 --> 03:21.200
"is if your delighted sons

03:21.300 --> 03:22.700
"turn it into
a three-day beer bash

03:22.800 --> 03:24.100
with go-go dancers."

03:25.600 --> 03:27.000
We, we wouldn't start there.

03:28.200 --> 03:31.600
All right, Cynthia's
in the ground, my face is on,

03:31.700 --> 03:34.000
I look stunning in black;

03:35.500 --> 03:37.000
Just follow my lead.

03:38.300 --> 03:39.900
Um, Mom...?

03:40.100 --> 03:40.900
Yes, dear.

03:46.300 --> 03:47.700
Alan thinks you're
a crazy she-bat

03:47.800 --> 03:49.400
and no one will mourn
at your funeral either

03:53.200 --> 03:55.700
We're telling you this
because we love you.

03:57.000 --> 03:58.200
I see.

03:58.500 --> 04:01.000
Look, Mom, you have to realize

04:01.100 --> 04:03.800
that you're not that
different from Cynthia.

04:04.000 --> 04:06.200
I most certainly am!

04:06.400 --> 04:08.700
Come on, Mom,
you speak ill of everyone,

04:08.800 --> 04:10.300
even your
closest friends.

04:10.400 --> 04:11.700
You, you manipulate people,

04:11.800 --> 04:13.900
you're an unbelievable
narcissist,

04:13.900 --> 04:15.100
you're self-obsessed...

04:15.200 --> 04:16.800
That's a bit redundant,
isn't it?

04:17.100 --> 04:19.399
You find fault with everything,

04:20.700 --> 04:22.500
...and frankly,
I don't know anyone

04:22.600 --> 04:24.300
who enjoys spending time
with you,

04:24.400 --> 04:26.500
let alone would cry
at your funeral.

04:27.700 --> 04:30.000
That's one point of view.

04:34.800 --> 04:35.600
Charlie,

04:35.800 --> 04:37.700
I notice you haven't said
anything.

04:39.100 --> 04:41.800
Actually, "crazy
she-bat" was mine.

04:45.000 --> 04:46.700
Again, Mom,
we're only telling you this

04:46.800 --> 04:48.900
because we care about you,
right, Charlie?

04:49.000 --> 04:50.200
We care about you.

04:50.400 --> 04:52.600
And, and it's not too late
for you to change

04:52.700 --> 04:54.300
and become the kind
of person that people

04:54.400 --> 04:55.700
would dearly miss.

04:56.000 --> 04:56.800
When you're dead.

05:00.200 --> 05:01.700
You've given me a lot
to think about.

05:02.100 --> 05:04.800
Yes, and, and while you're
thinking, remember the spirit

05:04.900 --> 05:06.000
in which it was intended.

05:07.000 --> 05:08.600
Oh, I won't forget that.

05:11.100 --> 05:12.000
Good, good.

05:12.200 --> 05:15.000
Listen, um, I think I'm gonna
beg off dinner tonight.

05:15.100 --> 05:16.700
Good, good. Aw...

05:20.700 --> 05:22.100
Good-bye, boys.

05:22.300 --> 05:23.600
Bye-bye.
Bye.

05:29.900 --> 05:30.900
Okay.

05:31.000 --> 05:31.800
"Okay"?

05:33.300 --> 05:35.400
What's okay?
What do you see that's okay?

05:35.900 --> 05:37.700
Well, we got out of dinner.

05:38.000 --> 05:39.700
Yes, but at what cost?

05:40.000 --> 05:42.100
Sure, her feelings are hurt
right now,

05:42.200 --> 05:44.100
but that'll pass in time,

05:44.400 --> 05:45.800
and then she'll see this

05:45.900 --> 05:48.200
as an opportunity
to grow and change.

05:48.600 --> 05:50.300
Do you actually believe that?

05:51.400 --> 05:52.900
I have to, Charlie.

05:54.800 --> 05:56.000
I have to.

05:58.400 --> 06:00.300
<i>* Men. *</i>

06:00.800 --> 06:02.900
Yo, mad props
on the sandwich, Dad.

06:03.000 --> 06:04.800
This PB and J is off the hook.

06:06.900 --> 06:07.600
Excuse me?

06:08.200 --> 06:10.300
<i>He's been watching MTV Cribs.</i>

06:12.300 --> 06:13.800
The kid's a sponge.

06:14.000 --> 06:15.600
For shizzle, my dizzle.

06:16.700 --> 06:18.400
Hey, MC Skidmark.

06:20.300 --> 06:22.400
Here's something else
you left in your pants.

06:24.500 --> 06:26.700
Oh, right, I was supposed
to mail this.

06:27.000 --> 06:28.200
What is it?
It's a birthday card

06:28.300 --> 06:30.000
Mom gave me to send to Grandma.

06:30.700 --> 06:33.500
Oh, God! Today's Mom's birthday.

06:33.700 --> 06:35.800
You forgot Mom's birthday?

06:36.400 --> 06:37.300
Did you remember it?

06:37.400 --> 06:40.000
Hey, hey, no one expects me
to remember anything.

06:41.400 --> 06:42.900
Whe's the last time
you talked to her?

06:43.000 --> 06:44.300
I don't know;
probably when we told her

06:44.400 --> 06:46.400
she's a horrible person
and nobody likes her.

06:46.500 --> 06:48.400
Oh, yeah, that was a fun day.

06:49.100 --> 06:51.200
I guess I could save
this for next year.

06:51.300 --> 06:53.400
No, no, no, you'll give it
to her in person.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.000
We'll go out,
we'll buy her present,

06:55.100 --> 06:56.000
and then we'll bring it to her.

06:56.300 --> 06:58.400
Gee, Alan, she hasn't talked
to us in weeks.

06:58.500 --> 07:00.800
Don't you think showing up
with a gift my jeopardize that?

07:01.400 --> 07:02.400
We have to go.
If we don't show up,

07:02.500 --> 07:03.600
we'll never
hear the end of it.

07:03.700 --> 07:04.600
True dat.

07:06.300 --> 07:07.900
You tell 'em, Poop Dog.

07:10.500 --> 07:12.700
Yo, check out
the bling.

07:14.700 --> 07:16.200
Jake, I'm not going
to tell you again.

07:16.300 --> 07:17.600
You're a pasty white kid.

07:17.700 --> 07:19.100
Start acting like one.

07:19.500 --> 07:20.500
Fine.

07:21.200 --> 07:22.300
Oh, this is cool.

07:25.200 --> 07:26.800
It does say "Mom."

07:27.300 --> 07:28.300
Charlie, be serious.

07:28.400 --> 07:30.200
Jake, if you really want
to help, try to find something

07:30.300 --> 07:32.200
that's more appropriate
for your grandma.

07:32.200 --> 07:33.000
Like what?

07:33.500 --> 07:36.500
See if they got a
grizzly bear ripping
apart a salmon.

07:40.000 --> 07:41.200
Hi, there.

07:41.300 --> 07:42.700
May I help you find something?

07:43.000 --> 07:44.400
Oh, yeah, we're, uh,
we're looking

07:44.500 --> 07:45.700
for a birthd gift
for our mother.

07:45.800 --> 07:47.700
Oh, how sweet.
When's her birthday?

07:48.200 --> 07:49.100
Today.

07:49.200 --> 07:49.900
Oh.

07:50.000 --> 07:51.100
He forgot.

07:51.600 --> 07:53.800
Well, um, tell me something
about her.

07:53.900 --> 07:54.700
What does she like?

07:54.800 --> 07:55.700
Hurting people.

07:57.300 --> 07:57.900
Charlie...

07:58.000 --> 07:59.700
It's a little hard
to answer that

07:59.800 --> 08:01.900
because we have a bit of
a strained relationship.

08:02.300 --> 08:04.300
Oh, so you'd like
to find a gift

08:04.400 --> 08:06.400
that would help bring you
closer together.

08:06.700 --> 08:08.000
Oh, no, no.
No, no, no.

08:10.000 --> 08:12.300
This is just your standard
family obligation,

08:12.400 --> 08:13.400
"Here it is,
Happy Birthday

08:13.500 --> 08:15.000
stay off our backs"
kind of thing.

08:16.000 --> 08:17.200
But with a pretty bow.

08:18.700 --> 08:22.000
I see.
And what is your price range?

08:22.200 --> 08:25.400
Uh, enough that she can't
complain, but not so much

08:25.500 --> 08:27.000
that it's worth her
while to return it.

08:27.100 --> 08:28.000
Exactly.

08:29.200 --> 08:30.400
Have you considered

08:30.500 --> 08:32.600
a nice perfume?

08:32.700 --> 08:33.799
Do you know
her scent?

08:33.900 --> 08:35.200
Oh, actually, I don't.

08:35.299 --> 08:36.000
I do.
You do?

08:36.100 --> 08:39.200
Yep. Do you carry
Chanel No. 666?

08:40.799 --> 08:43.600
You know, I think
I'm going to let
the two of you

08:43.700 --> 08:47.600
just browse a bit more
and I'll be back... maybe.

08:49.000 --> 08:50.100
Great news.

08:50.800 --> 08:52.000
It's on sale!

08:54.500 --> 08:55.900
<i>* Men. *</i>

08:56.400 --> 08:58.500
Now, remember, this was not
a last-minute thing.

08:58.600 --> 09:00.700
Our plan all along
was to surprise her.

09:00.800 --> 09:02.700
I know how to lie, Dad.

09:03.500 --> 09:05.400
We're not lying.
We're being considerate.

09:05.600 --> 09:06.700
By lying.

09:09.600 --> 09:11.300
Happy Birthday!

09:11.800 --> 09:13.600
Oh, what a surprise.

09:13.700 --> 09:15.600
That was the plan all along.

09:17.600 --> 09:19.200
I don't knowhat to say.

09:19.300 --> 09:21.300
After the last time we spoke,
I assumed...

09:21.400 --> 09:22.900
Oh, come on, Mom.

09:23.000 --> 09:24.300
No matter what,
you're still our mother.

09:24.400 --> 09:26.300
Right, Charlie?
You're still our mother.

09:28.100 --> 09:29.600
Give her her
present, Jake.

09:29.800 --> 09:30.700
Happy Birthday.

09:30.800 --> 09:31.800
Thank you.

09:32.100 --> 09:33.000
Oh, it's heavy.

09:33.100 --> 09:34.000
It's just a bowl.

09:34.100 --> 09:36.500
I wanted to get you
a bear-eating fish.

09:37.500 --> 09:40.300
But we got her a nice
crystal bowl instead.

09:42.100 --> 09:43.200
So, can we come in?

09:43.300 --> 09:45.300
Actually, I'm having
a little party.

09:45.400 --> 09:46.500
A party?!

09:46.600 --> 09:47.900
And you didn't invite us?

09:48.100 --> 09:51.300
Charles, if someone's not going
to mourn at my funeral,

09:51.400 --> 09:53.600
I certainly don't want them
at my birthday party.

09:54.800 --> 09:55.800
Then who's here?

09:57.700 --> 09:58.600
People who love me.

09:58.700 --> 10:01.200
People who care about me
and accept me for who I am.

10:02.600 --> 10:04.300
Oh, I got to see this.

10:05.000 --> 10:06.400
Please come in.

10:09.300 --> 10:10.400
Oh, hello.

10:11.900 --> 10:12.600
Hi.

10:12.800 --> 10:15.800
Charlie, Alan, Jake,
I'd like you to meet

10:15.900 --> 10:19.100
Roger and Philip
and their son Changpu.

10:19.300 --> 10:21.000
These are my sons
and grandson.

10:21.300 --> 10:22.700
Nice to meet you.
Hello.

10:22.800 --> 10:25.200
Your mom is such
an incredible woman.

10:25.300 --> 10:27.300
She's like the loving
mother I never had.

10:27.500 --> 10:29.200
She's fabulous!

10:29.300 --> 10:30.700
We're one big
happy family.

10:34.700 --> 10:37.700
Son of a bitch,
she got new people.

10:40.800 --> 10:42.200
Who are these guys?

10:42.400 --> 10:44.000
You're surprised
I have friends?

10:44.100 --> 10:45.600
You're surprised
that I'm surprised?

10:46.500 --> 10:48.400
Roger works in
my real estate office,

10:48.400 --> 10:50.800
Philip does my hair
and I introduced them.

10:50.900 --> 10:52.300
They make a lovely
couple, don't they?

10:52.500 --> 10:53.700
Yeah, I guess.

10:53.800 --> 10:55.100
And they adopted...

10:56.100 --> 10:56.900
...Chung King?

10:58.400 --> 11:01.100
Changpu.
Yes-- from China.

11:01.200 --> 11:02.600
Of course I had
to help them a bit,

11:02.700 --> 11:04.900
you know, greasing
the bureaucratic wheels.

11:05.000 --> 11:06.100
You bribed someone?

11:06.200 --> 11:07.500
Oh, don't be ridiculous.

11:07.600 --> 11:09.000
I merely slept with
a Commie.

11:11.100 --> 11:12.400
Is this goose liver?

11:12.500 --> 11:14.500
It's quail pate
with endive.

11:14.600 --> 11:15.700
Philip's special recipe.

11:15.800 --> 11:16.800
Oh, you gotta
give it to me.

11:16.900 --> 11:18.000
I'll trade you.

11:18.000 --> 11:19.600
My recipe for
your mother.

11:20.000 --> 11:20.900
Done.

11:21.800 --> 11:23.200
You are so lucky.

11:23.300 --> 11:25.800
My mother is aitch on wheels.

11:25.900 --> 11:27.300
Your mother?
What about my mother?

11:27.400 --> 11:29.100
Fine, your mother's
a bitch, too.

11:29.200 --> 11:30.200
* Thank you. *

11:31.800 --> 11:34.100
So do you have
PlayStation or an Xbox?

11:35.000 --> 11:36.100
I have a cello.

11:36.900 --> 11:38.200
What do you play
on that?

11:38.300 --> 11:41.500
Beethoven, Brahms,
Bach, Shostakovich.

11:41.600 --> 11:43.600
<i>So, no Grand Theft Auto?</i>

11:47.700 --> 11:53.500
* Happy birthday to you *

11:53.600 --> 11:57.800
* Happy birthday
to you *

