Well, that was one of
the most bizarre evenings

13:13.700 --> 13:14.700
I've ever spent.

13:15.100 --> 13:16.400
It was right up there.

13:16.500 --> 13:18.300
I thought it was fabulous.

13:21.800 --> 13:23.200
You know what's
happened, don't you?

13:23.600 --> 13:24.700
We've been replaced.

13:25.500 --> 13:26.500
Fine with me.

13:26.700 --> 13:28.300
As long as she's got
Siegfried and Roy,

13:28.400 --> 13:29.700
we don't have to
deal with her anymore.

13:30.300 --> 13:31.500
Oh, it's fine with me, too.

13:31.600 --> 13:33.500
I just... I can't believe
she conned these guys

13:33.600 --> 13:35.100
into thinking
she's a good witch.

13:36.200 --> 13:37.200
Well, we know she's not.

13:41.100 --> 13:44.800
Hey, Spongebob GayPants,
take a break.

13:47.600 --> 13:49.000
You don't think
we might've been...

13:49.400 --> 13:51.000
wrong about Mom.

13:51.500 --> 13:52.200
What?!

13:52.300 --> 13:54.300
I'm just saying
that Roger and Philip

13:54.400 --> 13:56.200
obviously see something in her
that we don't.

13:56.600 --> 13:58.300
Who knows her better,
us or them?

13:58.400 --> 13:59.700
Well, us, no question.

14:00.000 --> 14:02.000
But maybe there's a part of her
we're missing.

14:02.100 --> 14:04.700
Alan, there's a part of her
she's missing.

14:04.700 --> 14:06.100
It's called her soul.

14:06.600 --> 14:07.700
Snap!

