14:19.200 --> 14:20.900
Hey, Mom, how are you?

14:21.100 --> 14:23.300
Charlie, what
a pleasant surprise.

14:23.400 --> 14:26.100
Oh, I was just calling to say
happy birthday again

14:26.200 --> 14:27.200
and thanks for last night.

14:27.300 --> 14:30.300
was so nice to meet Philip
and Roger and...

14:31.000 --> 14:32.500
Shanghai.

14:33.100 --> 14:34.500
Changpu.

14:34.800 --> 14:37.600
And thank you for
the lovely crystal bowl.

14:37.800 --> 14:38.700
Oh, good-- you like it.

14:39.000 --> 14:40.700
Like it?
Well, I love it.

14:41.000 --> 14:42.700
I'm admiring it right now.

14:44.200 --> 14:45.600
Great. Great.

14:45.700 --> 14:47.000
Listen, dear,
I've really got to go.

14:47.100 --> 14:48.300
No, no, no,
wait, wait, wait, Mom.

14:48.500 --> 14:49.600
I want to clear the air

14:49.700 --> 14:51.500
about that stuff that got said
a couple of weeks ago.

14:51.800 --> 14:53.000
What's that?

14:53.500 --> 14:56.600
Well, I don't have any problems
with you being who you are.

14:56.700 --> 14:58.500
That whole thing about
you needing to change,

14:58.600 --> 15:01.000
well, that's Alan's deal.

15:02.000 --> 15:03.100
Oh, I knew that.

15:04.300 --> 15:06.600
Yeah, yeah, the thing that
I love about our relationship

15:06.600 --> 15:08.400
is that you don't try
to change me

15:08.500 --> 15:09.600
and I don't try to change you.

15:09.700 --> 15:13.200
We accept each other as, you
know, incapable of changing.

15:13.300 --> 15:14.900
That is very sweet.

15:15.000 --> 15:17.800
Okay, here you go:
eggs Benedict.

15:17.800 --> 15:19.300
My own recipe.

15:20.100 --> 15:21.100
Anything else?

15:21.200 --> 15:22.300
No, no, I guess not.

15:23.500 --> 15:24.400
Love you.

15:24.500 --> 15:25.600
You, too.

15:25.600 --> 15:26.500
Bye-bye.

15:27.300 --> 15:28.300
Who was that?

15:28.400 --> 15:29.900
Oh, nobody.

15:30.900 --> 15:33.100
Now, you said there
was something important

15:33.200 --> 15:34.400
you wanted to talk to me about.

15:34.500 --> 15:35.400
Yeah, yeah.

15:35.500 --> 15:37.100
I was just thinking about.

15:37.200 --> 15:38.900
Mm, too much lemon juice
in the hollandaise sauce.

15:39.000 --> 15:40.300
Oh, gee, I'm sorry.

15:40.800 --> 15:42.800
You should ask Philip
for his recipe.

15:43.800 --> 15:44.700
I will.

15:45.000 --> 15:48.000
You might also ask him
who cuts his hair.

15:48.300 --> 15:50.500
You don't have to be gay
to look nice.

15:53.500 --> 15:54.400
I'll ask.

15:54.500 --> 15:57.200
Um, anyway, I just wanted
to clear the air

15:57.300 --> 15:58.500
about a few things.

15:58.700 --> 16:00.600
Really? Like what?

16:01.600 --> 16:03.300
Well, you know, that, uh...

16:03.400 --> 16:06.400
that stuff that got said
a couple of weeks ago.

16:07.300 --> 16:09.100
I just want you to know...

16:09.800 --> 16:11.200
it was Charlie'ea.

16:12.200 --> 16:13.300
Oh, I knew that.

16:14.700 --> 16:16.800
Yeah, I only went along
because, you know,

16:17.100 --> 16:18.200
he's the older
brother and...

16:19.300 --> 16:20.700
he might've been drunk.

16:21.600 --> 16:24.400
Well, I'm just glad one of
my sons cares about me.

16:24.500 --> 16:25.900
I do. I love you, Mommy.

16:28.000 --> 16:29.000
Right back at ya.

16:29.700 --> 16:30.500
Now, skidaddle.

16:30.600 --> 16:32.200
Philip and Roger will
be here any minute.

16:32.800 --> 16:34.600
Oh, okay.

16:37.000 --> 16:40.100
Oh, look,
there they are.

16:40.600 --> 16:42.600
Philip, Roger and Changpu.

16:44.300 --> 16:47.300
No pictures of me or Jake?

16:47.900 --> 16:51.800
Sweetheart, I've been asking for
a decent picture for years.

16:52.000 --> 16:54.300
All I've ever gotten
was a school photo of Jake

16:54.400 --> 16:56.400
where he appeared to be
sucking on his shirt.

16:56.800 --> 16:59.400
Oh, yeah, they served spaghetti
on picture day.

17:00.800 --> 17:02.500
Oh, hey, you know what
we should do?

17:03.100 --> 17:06.000
We should get together and
take a nice family portrait.

17:06.099 --> 17:07.099
That sounds lovely.

17:07.200 --> 17:09.099
Great! I'll set it up!
Terrific!

17:09.300 --> 17:11.000
Okay, bye.

17:11.599 --> 17:12.500
Bye-bye.

17:14.500 --> 17:16.900
Um, d I tell you
that I love you, Mommy?

17:17.800 --> 17:20.099
Yes, but I never tire
of hearing it.

17:20.300 --> 17:23.099
Oh, well, in that case, uh,
I love you, Mommy.

17:29.000 --> 17:31.700
I really should have stopped
drinking during pregnancy.

17:35.300 --> 17:37.200
<i>* Men. *</i>

17:48.300 --> 17:49.000
Hello?

17:49.600 --> 17:50.400
Hello.

17:57.300 --> 17:58.100
Hey, Alan?

17:58.200 --> 17:58.900
Yeah?

18:00.300 --> 18:01.400
I couldn't help noticing

18:01.500 --> 18:03.500
there's a photographer
in the living room.

18:03.600 --> 18:05.400
Oh. Yeah, we're, uh...

18:05.500 --> 18:06.500
we're taking
a family picture.

18:07.300 --> 18:08.500
Family picture?

18:10.300 --> 18:11.600
Would it be rude of me
to point out

18:11.700 --> 18:13.400
the obvious flaw in your plan?

18:14.600 --> 18:16.200
I didn't think
you'd be interested.

18:16.300 --> 18:16.900
I'm not.

18:18.400 --> 18:21.600
So, it's just you and Little
Lord Scratch 'n' Sniff?

18:22.400 --> 18:23.700
Hey, if you don't
sniff it,

18:23.800 --> 18:25.200
you don't know
what it is.

18:29.400 --> 18:32.600
Actually, it's a picture
of me, Jake d Mom.

18:33.600 --> 18:34.800
Mom?!

18:35.100 --> 18:36.100
Mom who?

18:37.100 --> 18:39.800
She said she didn't have
any good pictures of us.

18:41.000 --> 18:42.800
Wait a minute.
When did you talk to Mom?

18:43.000 --> 18:43.700
I...

18:44.900 --> 18:46.000
She called me.

18:47.200 --> 18:49.700
You've been sucking up to her
behind my back, haven't you?

18:50.600 --> 18:54.200
Charlie, you have no idea
how insane that sounds.

18:56.100 --> 18:58.300
All I know is after everything
that's happened,

18:58.400 --> 19:01.200
I would never talk to her
without talking to you first.

19:01.300 --> 19:02.000
You wouldn't?

19:03.000 --> 19:04.600
What kind of person
do you take me f?

19:04.700 --> 19:06.000
I'd rather cut off my arm

19:06.100 --> 19:09.400
than pick up the phone and try
to undermine my own brother.

19:10.300 --> 19:11.200
Me, too.

19:12.100 --> 19:13.200
That's why I'm...

19:14.300 --> 19:16.300
taking a bullet here
for the both of us.

19:16.800 --> 19:17.300
Oh.

19:18.200 --> 19:19.800
Well, thanks.

19:20.000 --> 19:21.300
You don't have to thank me...

19:22.300 --> 19:23.400
I'm your brother.

19:25.200 --> 19:26.400
oh, Mommy's here.

19:28.400 --> 19:29.900
Might as well
get this over with.

19:30.800 --> 19:32.100
Wait a sec, hang on.

19:33.400 --> 19:34.500
Let me go change.

19:34.600 --> 19:36.100
You actually want to be
in the picture?

19:36.200 --> 19:37.800
No, no, no,
are you kidding?

19:39.300 --> 19:41.300
It's not fair for you
to have to do it alone.

19:42.000 --> 19:44.600
Oh... well, thanks.

19:45.000 --> 19:46.300
You don't have to thank me.

19:46.400 --> 19:47.600
I'm your brother.

19:51.200 --> 19:52.600
Hi, Mom.
Hello, dear.

19:53.000 --> 19:54.500
Hey, Mom, how are you?
Good to see you.

19:54.600 --> 19:55.600
Hi, Charlie.

19:55.800 --> 19:59.000
Oh, what a marvelous house.

19:59.100 --> 20:00.200
It's adorable.

20:01.000 --> 20:01.800
Mom?

20:02.000 --> 20:03.800
You said you wanted
a family portrait.

20:07.500 --> 20:09.600
Okay, well,
I'm going back to bed.

20:09.900 --> 20:11.300
Wait, Charlie,
what about the pictu?

20:11.600 --> 20:13.300
Put me down for a wallet size.

20:14.200 --> 20:16.400
???

20:39.700 --> 20:40.300
Like that?

20:40.400 --> 20:42.700
Yeah, but what was all that crap
in the beginning?

20:43.700 --> 20:46.000
It was an introduction
of my own composition.

20:46.800 --> 20:48.300
Well, no offense,
but "Smoke on the Water"

20:48.400 --> 20:50.600
doesn't begin with crap
on the water.

20:52.300 --> 20:53.200
My apologies.

20:53.300 --> 20:55.000
Okay, let's take it
from the top.

20:55.400 --> 20:57.500
One, two, three, four.

21:06.300 --> 21:08.000
The playdate
was a good idea.

21:08.200 --> 21:11.300
Yeah, let's see how
Grandma likes her prodigy

21:11.400 --> 21:13.800
after he sponges up
our sponge.

